  "language": "en",
  "text": "Excuse me, sir. Sir, is this your Bugatti? How did you get a Bugatti? I haven't met you before. Yes, you have. How did you get a Bugatti, man? I bought it. What a lot of business are you in. I'm one of the biggest real estate developers in the world. Are you actually? We're building the Bugatti building right there. Growing up, did you think that that was ever going to be possible? No, I had a lot of Bugatti posters in my room, but never a Bugatti building. I didn't think so. Which made it a reality. If you have a lot of passion in life, you can achieve a lot of things you thought were dreams. What was the most amount of money that you've made in a single year? A lot. Give me a range. Almost $5 billion. $5 billion. In terms of sales, yeah. Do you think everybody's built for entrepreneurship? No. Why not? You're going to fail a lot of times. Did you ever get rejected in business? Oh, a thousand times. At one point in my life, I used to make 110 calls on average every day. I used to count them, actually. I still have screenshots, pitching to sell buildings, and the amount of times I was ghosted, ignored, rejected, got a big fat no. To be successful, you've got to be a good salesman. And a good salesman is able to take a no and still try again. But you've already made billions of dollars throughout your career. You're still building that you buy Skyline. Why is that? The biggest inspiration for success is success. So success always attracts more success. Remember how you used to grind from day one? Make sure you approach every day, even when you've made it, in the same energy, passion, and hunger. Because if you become complacent, that's the day you lose. You get comfortable. Somebody else is going to come take your business. Comfort is the most dangerous drug. An average is your biggest enemy to becoming success. We want greatness. Absolutely. How do you know? I'm 31. You're 31 years old? I am. I'm proud of you, man. Thank you very much. You inspired the hell out of me. I'm proud of you too. I mean, you're doing very well. Do you believe in God? Of course I do. Everything that happens in this life is in the hands of God. How did you know God was real? Because I saw a lot of miracles in my life. You know, I asked God for miracles in my life, and I saw them happen. A lot of prayers were answered. You've got amazing advice, sir. Thank you very much. Thank you so much, friend. I've got to give you a hug, man. And I'd like to connect with all the billionaires. Can I get your contact? Sure. Yeah, yeah. Of course. Absolutely.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 3.1,
      "text": "Excuse me, sir. Sir, is this your Bugatti?"
    },
    {
      "start": 3.5,
      "end": 4.5,
      "text": "How did you get a Bugatti?"
    },
    {
      "start": 4.7,
      "end": 5.4,
      "text": "I haven't met you before."
    },
    {
      "start": 5.6,
      "end": 6.0,
      "text": "Yes, you have."
    },
    {
      "start": 6.1,
      "end": 7.2,
      "text": "How did you get a Bugatti, man?"
    },
    {
      "start": 7.3,
      "end": 7.8,
      "text": "I bought it."
    },
    {
      "start": 8.3,
      "end": 9.5,
      "text": "What a lot of business are you in."
    },
    {
      "start": 9.7,
      "end": 11.6,
      "text": "I'm one of the biggest real estate developers in the world."
    },
    {
      "start": 11.8,
      "end": 12.4,
      "text": "Are you actually?"
    },
    {
      "start": 12.8,
      "end": 14.4,
      "text": "We're building the Bugatti building right there."
    },
    {
      "start": 14.6,
      "end": 16.6,
      "text": "Growing up, did you think that that was ever going to be possible?"
    },
    {
      "start": 16.8,
      "end": 20.2,
      "text": "No, I had a lot of Bugatti posters in my room, but never a Bugatti building."
    },
    {
      "start": 20.3,
      "end": 20.9,
      "text": "I didn't think so."
    },
    {
      "start": 21.1,
      "end": 21.8,
      "text": "Which made it a reality."
    },
    {
      "start": 22.0,
      "end": 24.8,
      "text": "If you have a lot of passion in life, you can achieve a lot of things you thought"
    },
    {
      "start": 24.8,
      "end": 25.3,
      "text": "were dreams."
    },
    {
      "start": 25.5,
      "end": 27.8,
      "text": "What was the most amount of money that you've made in a single year?"
    },
    {
      "start": 28.0,
      "end": 28.3,
      "text": "A lot."
    },
    {
      "start": 28.5,
      "end": 29.0,
      "text": "Give me a range."
    },
    {
      "start": 29.0,
      "end": 30.0,
      "text": "Almost $5 billion."
    },
    {
      "start": 30.7,
      "end": 31.3,
      "text": "$5 billion."
    },
    {
      "start": 31.9,
      "end": 32.9,
      "text": "In terms of sales, yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 33.0,
      "end": 34.3,
      "text": "Do you think everybody's built for entrepreneurship?"
    },
    {
      "start": 34.7,
      "end": 34.9,
      "text": "No."
    },
    {
      "start": 35.1,
      "end": 35.3,
      "text": "Why not?"
    },
    {
      "start": 35.8,
      "end": 37.0,
      "text": "You're going to fail a lot of times."
    },
    {
      "start": 37.2,
      "end": 38.2,
      "text": "Did you ever get rejected in business?"
    },
    {
      "start": 38.5,
      "end": 39.7,
      "text": "Oh, a thousand times."
    },
    {
      "start": 40.2,
      "end": 43.6,
      "text": "At one point in my life, I used to make 110 calls on average every day."
    },
    {
      "start": 43.7,
      "end": 44.6,
      "text": "I used to count them, actually."
    },
    {
      "start": 44.7,
      "end": 49.1,
      "text": "I still have screenshots, pitching to sell buildings, and the amount of times I was"
    },
    {
      "start": 49.1,
      "end": 52.0,
      "text": "ghosted, ignored, rejected, got a big fat no."
    },
    {
      "start": 52.2,
      "end": 53.9,
      "text": "To be successful, you've got to be a good salesman."
    },
    {
      "start": 54.0,
      "end": 57.0,
      "text": "And a good salesman is able to take a no and still try again."
    },
    {
      "start": 57.0,
      "end": 59.2,
      "text": "But you've already made billions of dollars throughout your career."
    },
    {
      "start": 59.3,
      "end": 60.6,
      "text": "You're still building that you buy Skyline."
    },
    {
      "start": 60.7,
      "end": 61.3,
      "text": "Why is that?"
    },
    {
      "start": 61.5,
      "end": 63.7,
      "text": "The biggest inspiration for success is success."
    },
    {
      "start": 64.2,
      "end": 66.3,
      "text": "So success always attracts more success."
    },
    {
      "start": 66.6,
      "end": 68.8,
